Uses of Interface
com.noctarius.tengi.core.connection.Transport

  • Packages that use Transport 
    Package Description
    com.noctarius.tengi.client
    The client package contains classes necessary to create a client instance inside applications.
    com.noctarius.tengi.core.config
    The config package contains the configuration interfaces and a ConfigurationBuilder for creating immutable configuration that can easily be shared between threads.
    com.noctarius.tengi.core.connection
    The connection package contains the common interfaces to work with server or client connections.
    com.noctarius.tengi.server
    The server package contains classes necessary to create a server instance inside applications.
    com.noctarius.tengi.spi.connection
    The connection package contains interfaces and base-classes necessary to implement custom transports using the provided SPI.

      class  ClientTransport
      The ClientTransport enum defines built-in, client-side Transport implementations, however other implementations are still possible to be chosen.

      Methods in com.noctarius.tengi.core.config with parameters of type Transport 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      ConfigurationBuilder ConfigurationBuilder.addTransport(Transport... transports)
      Adds one or more Transports to the possible transports.
      ConfigurationBuilder ConfigurationBuilder.addTransport(Transport transport)
      Adds a Transport to the possible transports.
      int Configuration.getTransportPort(Transport transport)
      Returns either the explicitly configured or default port of the given transport.
      ConfigurationBuilder ConfigurationBuilder.transportPort(Transport transport, int port)
      Configures an explicit mapping of a port (for example TCP or UDP) to the given Transport.
